/*--><!]]>*/
</style><p>
The trouble with virtual reality (VR) is that science fiction and other popular media have so raised expectations that people are always disappointed, because they all think that fully functional VR is already here. But what VR is really good at is storytelling, simulator games, and training of all sorts.</p></div></div></div>
  <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="https://www.aaiforesight.com/blog/vr-and-ai-development" rel="tag" title="VR and AI Development">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about VR and AI Development</span></a></li>
